In 1992 a bill was introduced to the National Assembly with regulations that only allow abortion after rape only when it wasn’t reported within twenty-four hours. If the pregnancy resulted from consensual sex it is punishable by up to five years imprisonment. Accidental pregnancy from rape is pardoned (The Law data).

Due to the hostile attitude towards sex and the lack of sex education programs in Venezuela most educational programs for teenagers only reports to them the disadvantages of sex and how to abstain from sex with death. Less than three percent of young people know the proper use of condoms or the true opportunity for obtaining HIVu2103/ (The Law Map data). The sexual education must be improved to give strong sex education and contraceptive programs, which might help to reduce adolescent pregnancies.
